      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial aspect of the 14th Amendment that has been instrumental in expanding civil rights and personal liberties. By striking down laws that infringe on fundamental rights, such as those found in the Bill of Rights, the Supreme Court has consistently demonstrated its commitment to protecting individual freedoms. Notably, landmark cases like Griswold v. Connecticut (1965) and Roe v. Wade (1973) have utilized substantive due process to safeguard reproductive rights and intimate autonomy. These rulings have significantly advanced the cause of civil rights and personal liberties in the United States.",
